"Personal use" means use by a single individual:
  (a) for that individual's own private benefit;
  (b) not on behalf of any company, organization, government, or
      other entity;
  (c) not in connection with any revenue-generating activity, paid
      consulting, or work performed for compensation;
  (d) where no other person has access to the Software's outputs as
      part of their work.

A solopreneur or independent person running their own knowledge brain
on their own machine is using the Software personally, and may do so
for free.

================================================================
2. Commercial Use — Paid License Required
================================================================

Any use of the Software not falling within Section 1 is "commercial
use" and requires a paid commercial license obtained from pergamino.ai.

The commercial license fee is **USD $100 per User, per year**, payable
in advance, beginning on the date the Software is first used commercially.

A "User" is any natural person who, during the license year:
  (a) has read or write access to any vault, scope, or canon
      provisioned with the Software (whether on their own device,
      through a shared deployment, or via a hosted interface); or
  (b) receives outputs of the Software as part of their work (whether
      in chat, dashboard, message, or document form).

Headcount is measured as the maximum simultaneous count of such
persons during the license year. Bots, automated agents, and service
accounts do not count as Users.

To obtain a commercial license, contact: licensing@pergamino.ai

Until a commercial license is obtained and paid, commercial use is
not authorized under this license.

